<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4565448>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "Figure 10. Matsucoccus gallicolus Morrison. Third-instar male. Cooper River, Charleston, South Carolina, April 4, 1909, on Pinus taeda, S.G. Sanders. A) Apical four antennal segments. B) short filamentous seta. C) Thoracic spiracle. D) Hind tibia, tarsus, and claw. E) 1st abdominal spiracle. F) Long filamentous seta. G) 6th abdominal spiracle. H) Bilocular tubular ducts. I) Short dorsal filamentous seta." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4565448/files/figure.png" .

